
[1]penurious

   PENU'RIOUS, a. [L.penuria, scarcity, want; Gr. poor; rare.]

   1. Excessively saving or sparing in the use of money; parsimonious to a
   fault; sordid; as a penurious man. It expresses somewhat less than
   niggardly.

   2. Scanty; affording little; as a penurious spring.
